Text.Value: *You would wield a silver sword, ride a red dragon of your own. You would not just be ascended - you would be kith'rak.*
*You gave her everything - yet she's turned your own people against you, just as the dream figure warned.*
*Silver swords stained with shimmering ghaik blood - a comforting notion. Your queen is eternal and your people untouchable.*
*Her words were carved in slate and her figure carved in granite. She was silver, she was iron, she was your reason for being.*
*Yet even within reverie, the figure's final words penetrate as a silver sword into illithid flesh:*
*Vlaakith will stop at nothing to retrieve the Prism - even if it means sacrificing Lae'zel of K'liir, her most faithful champion.*
Heresy. Your queen bears the might of the Astral Sea. The ghaik are no threat to the githyanki.
*'I know a secret that Vlaakith never wants to be revealed.'*
*Moonrise is your destiny. That is where the truth will finally out.*
If the figure holds the power to resist illithid control, you must return it to Vlaakith.
*What must you do next?*
Lies, every word of it. Ghaik trickery played on you by the parasite in your head.
*It was in Vlaakith's name that you learned the art of the blade. It was by her protocol that you sought purification.*
Lies, every word of it. Ghaik trickery played on you by the parasite in your head.
The zaith'isk failed. Your people have turned on you. There must be truth in the figure's words.
*Could the Undying Queen truly be powerless against the Illithid Empire, as the dream figure said?*
*But now? Now, doubt gnaws at your skull like a tadpole gnaws at its host.*
*You want little more to rid yourself of the ghaik tadpole in your head.*
*'Queen Vlaakith is lying to you and your people.'*

EditorData.logicalname: Didn't try to kill Daisy twice

Text.Value: *'You were on the right path - to Moonrise Towers. Return to it.'*
*Vlaakith is afraid. Afraid of what you might discover. Afraid of you. And your most reliable ally lives inside the Prism you carry.*
*You were taught that she would reward her most vicious adepts with ascension - an invitation to the imperial city of Tu'narath.*
This figure is protecting you from the Absolute. He is an ally - and worth hearing out.
This figure is protecting you from the Absolute. She is an ally - and worth hearing out.
This figure is protecting you from the Absolute. They are an ally - and worth hearing out.
*Now, doubt gnaws at you like a tadpole at its host.*
*Now your own people point their blades at you, Lae'zel of K'liir, Vlaakith's most faithful warrior - just as your dream figure warned.*
*You did as the Undying Queen asked.*
*Let Vlaakith's servants come for you if they dare. You will show them who embodies the true essence of the githyanki.*
*The figure bid you to journey to Moonrise Towers. That is your destiny. That is where the truth will finally out.*
*Whoever this dream figure, one thing is clear: Vlaakith would sacrifice her own faithful to slay him.*
*Whoever this dream figure, one thing is clear: Vlaakith would sacrifice her own faithful to slay her.*
*Whoever this dream figure, one thing is clear: Vlaakith would sacrifice her own faithful to slay them.*
*Even faith is no shield when it's your own goddess who would shatter you.*
*As a young warrior on K'liir, you'd never once questioned your queen.*
*These were the words of your dream figure. Not long ago, they pierced the ethereal stillness of the Astral Plane.*
This secret is not yours to know. You will return the Astral Prism to Vlaakith and regain her favour.
Return the Astral Prism to Vlaakith and regain her favour.
Look for a way back into the Prism and ask the dream figure what she knows.
Look for a way back into the Prism and ask the dream figure what he knows.
Look for a way back into the Prism and ask the dream figure what they know.
*'Vlaakith, show us truth. Vlaakith, make me pure. Vlaakith, I seek entry. Vlaakith, I am reborn.'*
*Vlaakith knows this too. Perhaps the zaith'isk will cleanse you - or perhaps the Undying Queen will see that it kills you.*
*What secret could be so ruinous to the Undying Queen of the Six Arms of Tu'narath?*
*Your mind bursts with vicious images of githyanki knights tearing through scores of mind flayers.*
Your people have turned on you. There must be truth in the figure's words.
*Your people seek your head, just as the dream figure warned. Whatever this secret, Vlaakith will kill her own faithful to keep it.*
*What is this Astral Prism? Who is this dream figure? And what makes Vlaakith so desperate to slay her?*
*What is this Astral Prism? Who is this dream figure? And what makes Vlaakith so desperate to slay him?*
*What is this Astral Prism? Who is this dream figure? And what makes Vlaakith so desperate to slay them?*
*If the ghaik empire should rise - if the Grand Design were to transpire - it could be the doom of your people.*
There's no telling - but your people have turned on you. Vlaakith is afraid of being found out.
*As long as you carry the Prism - and the one inside - you remain Vlaakith's prey.*
*Blasphemous words, looming as large in your mind as the towering figure of Vlaakith herself.*
*You entered the Astral Prism. You attacked the one inside.*
*For now, the answers are locked tightly away. But there is one thing you are most certain of:*
*Questions gnaw at your mind like a tadpole at its host.*
*Such a feat would surely earn your queen's most gracious blessings.*
*And come, they most certainly will. Whoever this dream figure, Vlaakith would clearly sacrifice her own faithful to slay him.*
*And come, they most certainly will. Whoever this dream figure, Vlaakith would clearly sacrifice her own faithful to slay her.*
*And come, they most certainly will. Whoever this dream figure, Vlaakith would clearly sacrifice her own faithful to slay them.*
*You breathe slowly and deeply, seeking refuge from the figure's deceit in the words of the sacred Tla'ket.*
*But even in reverie, worry gnaws at you like a tadpole at its host.*
Do what you do best: fight. Bleed your own people if they come for your head.
*You can carry yourself tall knowing you were loyal in both deed and intent. You are no heretic.*
*But even in reverie, doubt gnaws at you like a tadpole at its host.*
*'You must go to Moonrise Towers. That is where the cultists are gathering.'*
Find the zaith'isk inside the crche and cleanse yourself of the parasite.
*As a young warrior on K'liir, you devoted your life to your queen.*

Synopsis:
Avatar laezel contemplates everything that happened with Vlaakith at the creche.
